to the editor in beautiful minds can be reclaimed op ed march 10 courtenay m harding asserts that we should have the courage to provide the opportunity for mentally ill people to lead productive lives but the major reason 25 million americans do not get the kind of care that has been proved to work is that providing psychosocial rehabilitation costs more money than merely handing out medications the influence of drug companies has been responsible in part for the fact that biological models of psychiatry have eclipsed psychosocial models researchers report that psychosocial treatments combined with appropriate medications result in outcomes superior to either treatment given alone will we have the courage to provide the money needed to assist mentally ill people to lead productive lives elise l lev newark march 10 2002 the writer is an associate professor of nursing at rutgers university

